aniBsuSuBase.name: aniBsuSuBase
aniBsuSuBase.contactinfo: Postal: Aperto Networks Inc 1637 S Main Street Milpitas, California 95035 Tel: +1 408 719 9977
aniBsuSuBase.description: This group allows the users of the BSU to access some basic information about the SU through Proxy.

aniBsuSuBaseTable.name: aniBsuSuBaseTable
aniBsuSuBaseTable.description: This table accesses the attributes of each SU MAC interface through proxy.

aniBsuSuBaseEntry.name: aniBsuSuBaseEntry
aniBsuSuBaseEntry.description: Basic information for a single SU. An entry in this table exists for each SU that is connected to the BSU.

aniBsuSuNetworkAccess.name: aniBsuSuNetworkAccess
aniBsuSuNetworkAccess.description: This object controls whether the SU has access to the network or not.

aniBsuSuMaxHostSupport.name: aniBsuSuMaxHostSupport
aniBsuSuMaxHostSupport.description: This object identifies the total number of hosts that can be granted access through SU. For PacketWave 110/210, this value is limited to 5. PacketWave 120/220 can support upto 20 hosts. PacketWave 130/230 can support upto 254 hosts.

aniBsuSuTargetFreq.name: aniBsuSuTargetFreq
aniBsuSuTargetFreq.description: The objects displays the target frequency for a particular SU. It returns the SU target frequency in a string format.

aniBsuSuFrequencyTable.name: aniBsuSuFrequencyTable
aniBsuSuFrequencyTable.description: The objects displays the Frequency Table for a particular SU. It returns the SU frequency table in a string format.
